  2. End-to-End Data Flow (one turn)

  User message
     ↓
  build_turn_context (turn_context.py)
     ├─ sanitize surrogates / non-ASCII
     ├─ _restore_or_build_system_prompt → 3-tier prompt (stable + context + volatile)
     ├─ hydrate todo/nudge counters from history
     ├─ append user msg to `messages`
     ├─ preflight compression (rough token estimate vs threshold)
     ├─ pre_llm_call plugin hook (returns context to inject into user msg)
     └─ external memory prefetch
     ↓
  LOOP (api_call_count < max_iterations) ─────────────────┐
     ↓                                                     │
     ├─ drain /steer into last tool message               │
     ├─ build api_messages (inject memory + plugin ctx    │
     │   ONLY into the current user message, never        │
     │   into the cached system prompt)                   │
     ├─ apply Anthropic cache_control on system + last 3  │
     ├─ sanitize_api_messages (orphaned tool_calls)       │
     ├─ drop thinking-only assistant turns                │
     ├─ normalize whitespace + sort tool_call JSON keys   │
     ├─ build_kwargs via ProviderTransport                │
     ├─ apply_llm_request_middleware + pre_api_request    │
     │   plugin hook                                      │
     ├─ _interruptible_api_call (streaming or non-stream) │
     ├─ classify_api_error → retry / fallback / compress  │
     │                                                     │
     ├─ normalize_response → NormalizedResponse           │
     ├─ map finish_reason ("stop", "tool_calls",          │
     │   "length", "content_filter")                      │
     │                                                     │
     ├─ if finish_reason == "length" → continuation       │
     ├─ if tool_calls present:                            │
     │     validate tool name → repair / synthetic result │
     │     validate JSON args → retry up to 3x            │
     │     _cap_delegate_task_calls + _deduplicate        │
     │     _execute_tool_calls (concurrent if safe)       │
     │        ├─ per-call middleware + plugin block        │
     │        ├─ tool_guardrails.before_call               │
     │        ├─ checkpoint (write_file/patch/terminal)    │
     │        ├─ thread-pool dispatch + ContextVar prop    │
     │        └─ post-call result classification           │
     │                                                     │
     └─ else (text response) → break ───────────────────  │
